The paper deals with the problem of estimating frequency moments in data streams, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper presents a randomized algorithm for this problem and analyzes its space complexity. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the problem of estimating frequency moments is related to the field of streaming algorithms, which makes it likely to belong to the categories of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
